\DOC mk_cond

\TYPE {mk_cond : term * term * term -> term}

\SYNOPSIS
Constructs a conditional term.

\DESCRIBE
{mk_cond(`t`,`t1`,`t2`)} returns {`if t then t1 else t2`}.

\FAILURE
Fails with {mk_cond} if {t} is not of type {`:bool`} or if {t1} and {t2} are
of different types.

\SEEALSO
dest_cond, is_cond.

\ENDDOC
